# Aurora UI Overhaul — Implementation Plan

## Summary

Replace the SwiftUI-only layout with an AppKit-driven architecture:
- **Pure AppKit lifecycle** (`@NSApplicationMain`) — no SwiftUI App/Scene/WindowGroup
- **NSSplitViewController** for the main 2-pane layout (sidebar + content)
- **NSPageController** for horizontal workspace paging in the sidebar
- **New Profile model** for pinned tabs shared across workspaces
- **Inspector** left as-is (already working)
- **Edge-to-edge** custom styling, no liquid glass

## What Changes vs. What Stays

**Unchanged:**
- `Aurora/WebKit/*` — C bridge, AuroraWebView, WebViewPool, URLResolver, NewTabPageHTML
- `Aurora/Persistence/PersistenceController.swift` — minor additions only
- `Aurora/Persistence/Models/Tab.swift`, `HistoryEntry.swift`
- `Aurora/CommandBar/CommandBarView.swift` — re-hosted in new layout
- Inspector behavior — already working

**Deleted:**
- `Aurora/App/AuroraApp.swift` — replaced by `@NSApplicationMain` on AppDelegate
- `Aurora/App/ContentView.swift` — replaced by AppKit window controller
- `Aurora/Browser/BrowserSplitView.swift` — replaced by NSSplitViewController

**Heavily Modified:**
- `Aurora/App/AppDelegate.swift` — becomes `@NSApplicationMain`, owns window + split view
- `Aurora/Browser/BrowserState.swift` — add profile support, bookmark toggle state, unified content activation
- `Aurora/Sidebar/SidebarView.swift` — complete rewrite as workspace pager host
- `Aurora/Browser/NavigationBarView.swift` — remove sidebar toggle button (NSSplitViewController handles it)
- `Aurora/Browser/WebContentView.swift` — add lazy init + empty state
- `Aurora/Persistence/Models/Space.swift` — add bookmarks relationship
- `Aurora/Persistence/Models/Bookmark.swift` — add optional space relationship
- `Aurora/Persistence/Models/PinnedTab.swift` — move from Space to Profile relationship

**New Files:**
- `Aurora/Browser/BrowserWindowController.swift` — NSWindowController + NSSplitViewController
- `Aurora/Browser/ContentPaneView.swift` — SwiftUI content pane (URL bar + web content + command bar overlay)
- `Aurora/Sidebar/WorkspacePagerController.swift` — NSPageController wrapper for workspace paging
- `Aurora/Sidebar/WorkspacePageView.swift` — single workspace page (pinned grid, header, bookmarks, tabs)
- `Aurora/Sidebar/WorkspaceDockView.swift` — bottom bar with workspace icons + create button
- `Aurora/Sidebar/PinnedTabGridView.swift` — grid layout for pinned tabs
- `Aurora/Sidebar/BookmarksSectionView.swift` — toggleable bookmarks with folders
- `Aurora/Persistence/Models/Profile.swift` — new Profile model owning pinned tabs
- `Aurora/UI/Utilities/ColorExtensions.swift` — extract Color(hex:) from SidebarView

---

## Phase 1: AppKit Skeleton + Lifecycle Switch

**Goal:** Replace SwiftUI App lifecycle with pure AppKit. Create NSSplitViewController with two panes (sidebar + content). App launches with empty panes.

### 1.1 Create `BrowserWindowController.swift`
- `BrowserWindowController: NSWindowController` creates NSWindow:
  - `styleMask: [.titled, .closable, .miniaturizable, .resizable, .fullSizeContentView]`
  - `titlebarAppearsTransparent = true`, `titleVisibility = .hidden`
  - `backgroundColor = NSColor(red: 0.08, green: 0.08, blue: 0.08, alpha: 1)` (dark, no liquid glass)
- `BrowserSplitViewController: NSSplitViewController` with two items:
  - Sidebar: `NSSplitViewItem.sidebarWithViewController(sidebarHosting)` — 260pt default, 200pt min, 360pt max, collapsible
  - Content: standard `NSSplitViewItem` with `NSHostingController` — min 400pt, not collapsible
- Each pane wraps `NSHostingController` embedding SwiftUI views
- Pass `BrowserState` and `ModelContainer` via SwiftUI `.environment()`

### 1.2 Rewrite `AppDelegate.swift`
- Add `@NSApplicationMain` attribute
- Remove `@main` from AuroraApp.swift (delete the file)
- In `applicationDidFinishLaunching`:
  - Init WebKit bridge
  - Set dark appearance
  - Create `BrowserWindowController`, make key and order front
  - Set up `ModelContainer` from `PersistenceController.shared`
  - Seed default data
  - Load BrowserState from store
- Build menus programmatically via `NSMenu` (File, Edit, View, Developer)
  - View menu: Toggle Sidebar, Toggle Inspector
  - Developer menu: Toggle Web Inspector (Opt+Cmd+I)
  - File menu: New Tab (Cmd+T), Close Tab (Cmd+W), New Workspace
- Wire notification observers for actions

### 1.3 Delete `AuroraApp.swift` and `ContentView.swift`
- Move notification handling and onAppear logic into AppDelegate
- Move command bar overlay into ContentPaneView

### 1.4 Delete `BrowserSplitView.swift`
- `ProgressBarView` moves into `ContentPaneView`

### 1.5 Verify: App launches with two-pane split, sidebar collapsible

---

## Phase 2: Data Model Updates

**Goal:** Add Profile model, update relationships, add bookmark-workspace scoping.

### 2.1 Create `Profile.swift`
```swift
@Model final class Profile {
    @Attribute(.unique) var id: UUID
    var name: String
    var createdAt: Date
    @Relationship(deleteRule: .cascade, inverse: \PinnedTab.profile)
    var pinnedTabs: [PinnedTab] = []
    @Relationship(deleteRule: .nullify, inverse: \Space.profile)
    var spaces: [Space] = []
}
```

### 2.2 Update `PinnedTab.swift`
- Replace `var space: Space?` with `var profile: Profile?`
- Pinned tabs now belong to a Profile, shown in all workspaces under that profile

### 2.3 Update `Space.swift`
- Add `var profile: Profile?` relationship
- Add `@Relationship(deleteRule: .nullify, inverse: \Bookmark.space) var bookmarks: [Bookmark] = []`

### 2.4 Update `Bookmark.swift`
- Add `var space: Space?` — bookmarks can be scoped to a workspace (nil = global)

### 2.5 Update `PersistenceController.swift`
- Add `Profile` to ModelContainer schema
- Seed a default "Personal" profile with the three default spaces assigned to it
- Migrate: existing pinned tabs move to the default profile

### 2.6 Verify: Build succeeds, app launches, data seeds correctly

---

## Phase 3: BrowserState Extensions

**Goal:** Extend state for profiles, workspace bookmarks, unified content activation.

### 3.1 Add profile state
- `activeProfile: Profile?`
- `activeProfileID: UUID?`

### 3.2 Add bookmark toggle state
- `bookmarksVisiblePerSpace: [UUID: Bool]` — keyed by space ID

### 3.3 Unified content activation
- `activateContent(id: UUID, url: String, spaceID: UUID)` — handles Tab, PinnedTab, or Bookmark UUIDs
- WebView is created from pool on first activation (lazy init)
- `activeTabID` can now refer to any content type's UUID

### 3.4 Workspace management
- `createSpace(name:color:icon:in:)`, `deleteSpace(_:in:)` methods
- `loadFromStore` updated to load profiles and their spaces

### 3.5 Verify: Build succeeds

---

## Phase 4: Content Pane

**Goal:** Build the center pane with lazy WebView init, empty state, command bar overlay.

### 4.1 Create `ContentPaneView.swift`
```
ZStack {
    VStack(spacing: 0) {
        NavigationBarView().frame(height: 48)
        ProgressBarView()
        if activeTabID != nil {
            WebContentView(tabID:spaceID:)
        } else {
            EmptyContentView() // dark bg, Aurora branding
        }
    }
    if isCommandBarVisible {
        CommandBarOverlay()
    }
}
```

### 4.2 Update `WebContentView.swift`
- Add `EmptyContentView` for no-tab-selected state
- WebView created only when tab is activated (not on launch)
- On tab close: remove WebView from pool

### 4.3 Update `NavigationBarView.swift`
- Remove sidebar toggle button (NSSplitViewController handles it natively)
- Keep back/forward/reload/address bar

### 4.4 Verify: Build succeeds, content area shows empty state, shows web content on tab selection

---

## Phase 5: Sidebar — Workspace Pager

**Goal:** Replace the sidebar with horizontal-paging workspace carousel + bottom dock.

### 5.1 Create `WorkspacePagerController.swift`
- `NSPageController` subclass or wrapper
- Each page = one workspace's content (NSHostingController wrapping WorkspacePageView)
- Snap-to-page behavior (NSPageController handles this natively)
- Programmatic page switching when workspace is selected from dock
- Bind selectedIndex ↔ BrowserState.activeSpaceID

### 5.2 Create `WorkspacePageView.swift`
Single workspace page content (top to bottom):
```
ScrollView(.vertical) {
    VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 12) {
        PinnedTabGridView(pinnedTabs: profile.pinnedTabs)
        WorkspaceHeader(space: space, bookmarksVisible: $visible)
        if visible { BookmarksSectionView(bookmarks: space.bookmarks) }
        TabListView(tabs: space.tabs.sorted(by: order))
    }
}
```

### 5.3 Create `PinnedTabGridView.swift`
- `LazyVGrid(columns: [adaptive(minimum: 56)])` of pinned tab cells
- Each cell: favicon/globe icon + truncated title
- Indicator if WebView is active in pool
- On click: `browserState.activateContent(id:url:spaceID:)`

### 5.4 Create `BookmarksSectionView.swift`
- Group bookmarks by `folderName` (nil = ungrouped)
- Folders as disclosure groups
- Bookmark rows: icon + title, click to activate
- Optional WebView tie-in (same as pinned tabs)

### 5.5 Create `WorkspaceDockView.swift`
- Horizontal row of workspace icons (colored circles with SF Symbol)
- Active workspace: prominent/highlighted (larger, border)
- Tap: scroll pager to that workspace + set activeSpaceID
- "+" button: create new workspace

### 5.6 Rewrite `SidebarView.swift`
- New root: `VStack { WorkspacePagerHost (fills space) / Divider / WorkspaceDockView (52pt) }`
- `WorkspacePagerHost` = NSViewControllerRepresentable wrapping the NSPageController
- Extract `Color(hex:)` to `Aurora/UI/Utilities/ColorExtensions.swift`
- Delete old SpaceSwitcherView, SpaceChip, PinnedTabsView, TabRowView, SidebarBottomBar

### 5.7 Verify: Build succeeds, sidebar pages between workspaces, pinned tabs and bookmarks display correctly

---

## Phase 6: Integration & Polish

### 6.1 Wire menus to actions
- Cmd+T → new tab in active space
- Cmd+W → close active tab
- Cmd+L → focus address bar
- Cmd+K → toggle command bar
- Cmd+Shift+L → toggle sidebar
- Opt+Cmd+I → toggle inspector

### 6.2 Edge-to-edge styling
- All backgrounds: dark solid colors (no vibrancy/materials)
- Sidebar background: `#141414`
- Content background: `#1a1a1a`
- No system toolbar chrome visible
- Custom divider styling between panes

### 6.3 Final build verification
- `xcodebuild build` with zero errors
- App launches, shows sidebar with workspace pager
- Clicking a tab loads web content
- Workspace switching via dock and swipe works
- Command bar overlay functional
- Inspector toggle works

---

## Architecture Diagram

```
@NSApplicationMain AppDelegate
  └── BrowserWindowController (NSWindowController)
       └── BrowserSplitViewController (NSSplitViewController)
            ├── Sidebar Pane (NSHostingController)
            │    └── SidebarView (SwiftUI)
            │         ├── WorkspacePagerHost (NSViewControllerRepresentable)
            │         │    └── NSPageController
            │         │         └── WorkspacePageView per space (SwiftUI via NSHostingController)
            │         │              ├── PinnedTabGridView (profile-level)
            │         │              ├── Workspace Header + Bookmarks toggle
            │         │              ├── BookmarksSectionView
            │         │              └── TabListView
            │         └── WorkspaceDockView (workspace icons + create)
            │
            └── Content Pane (NSHostingController)
                 └── ContentPaneView (SwiftUI)
                      ├── NavigationBarView (back/fwd/reload/address)
                      ├── ProgressBarView
                      ├── WebContentView or EmptyContentView
                      └── CommandBarOverlay (conditional ZStack)

BrowserState (@Observable singleton) — all runtime state
WebViewPool (singleton) — WKContextRef per space, AuroraWebView per tab/pinned/bookmark
```
